        "pull_request": {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/axios/axios/pulls/7279",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7279",
          "diff_url": "https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7279.diff",
          "patch_url": "https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7279.patch",
          "merged_at": null
        },
        "body": "Fixed Issue #7271 \r\n\r\n**Description**\r\n\r\nThis PR removes CreateAxiosDefaults[\"lookup\"] in favor of using only Agent[\"lookup\"] for custom hostname resolution in Node.js. Axios already prioritizes Agent.lookup, and the Axios-level lookup option is redundant and poorly typed, leading to unnecessary duplication and complex validation logic.\r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n\r\n1. Poor typing & unnecessary complexity.\r\n2. There is also a major fix that CreateAxiosDefaults.lookup has loosely defined types.\r\n3. Custom DNS lookup is only supported in Node.js.\r\n4. Axios prefers Agent.lookup; CreateAxiosDefaults.lookup is only used if the agent does not define one.\r\n\r\n**Solution**\r\n\r\n1. Remove CreateAxiosDefaults[\"lookup\"]\r\n2. Now , Axios already prioritizes Agent[\"lookup\"] according to Node.js standards.\r\n\r\n### I also want to show the demonstrated example code for clarification for the review by maintainers\r\n\r\nCode Snippet 1\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst httpsAgent = new Agent({ lookup: dnsLookup });\r\n\r\naxios.create({\r\n  httpsAgent,\r\n  lookup: customWrappedLookup\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow , in the above code, problem is that there exists a duplicate logic as we are defining two lookup functions(dnsLookup and customWrappedLookup) so , it waill cause more bugs and consequently more confusion.\r\n\r\nCode Snippet 2:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst httpsAgent = new Agent({ lookup: dnsLookup });\r\n\r\naxios.create({\r\n  httpsAgent\r\n});\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow , in this code there is only one lookup function that is the Node.js provided us(Agent.lookup), so it, resulted in to more cleaner API, no more wrapping .\r\n\r\n**Please review and let me know if you'd like any modifications. I'm ready to update the PR.**\r\n\r\n",
